{"_at":[1775681788189,0],"_by":"darin@book","_v":{"acceptance_criteria":[[1775681219560,0],"darin@book"],"claim":[[1775681229439,0],"darin@book"],"description":[[1775681219560,0],"darin@book"],"design":[[1775681219560,0],"darin@book"],"estimated_minutes":[[1775681219560,0],"darin@book"],"external_ref":[[1775681219560,0],"darin@book"],"labels":[[1775681219560,0],"darin@book"],"priority":[[1775681219560,0],"darin@book"],"source_repo":[[1775681219560,0],"darin@book"],"title":[[1775681219560,0],"darin@book"],"type":[[1775681219560,0],"darin@book"]},"assignee":"darin@book","assignee_expires":1775684829439,"created_at":[1775681219560,0],"created_by":"darin@book","description":"**Problem**\n`bd ready` only considers direct `blocks` edges. If a sub-epic is blocked by an earlier stage, its leaf children still appear ready unless each leaf also gets explicit deps.\n\n**Design**\nMake blocked-state queries propagate active blockers down `parent` edges so blocked ancestors also block their descendants. Reuse the same helper for `ready` and other derived blocked surfaces.\n\n**Acceptance**\n- [ ] A blocked parent/sub-epic causes descendant leaves to be excluded from `bd ready`\n- [ ] Derived blocked/status surfaces stay consistent\n- [ ] Regression coverage exists at the owning layer\n\n**Files:** crates/beads-daemon/src/runtime/query_executor.rs, crates/beads-daemon/src/runtime/query_executor/helpers.rs","id":"beads-rs-rvlh","labels":{"cc":{"max":{}},"entries":{}},"priority":1,"status":"closed","title":"Cascade readiness blocking through parent descendants","type":"bug"}
